---
title: Maple-Glazed Chicken with Sweet Potato Mash and Green Beans
description: This recipe was made for anyone with an insatiable sweet tooth. You know, the eaters who usually need an extra nudge to eat their veggies. With cinnamon-spiced sweet potatoes and a maple syrup glaze, there will be no shortage of candy-like flavors on the plate, nor of nutrients like vitamin A. But because this is dinnertime, there are still savory elements to anchor it all, like white meat chicken and crisp, garlicky green beans.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/maple-glazed-chicken-f2f5fdf5.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/maple-glazed-chicken-7e65c52d.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/maple-glazed-chicken-59d68d31c94eac138308dec2
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 42 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 59 g
  sugar: 25 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 300 mg
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry all produce. Peel @sweet potatoes{4%ounce}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. Place
in a large #pot with enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil and cook until
easily pierced by a knife, ~{12-15%minutes}. Remove from #pot with a #slotted spoon.
Place in a large #bowl, keeping pot of boiling water on stove.

While sweet potatoes cook, heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a
large pan over medium-high heat. Season @chicken breasts{24%ounce} all over with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.
Remove from pan and set aside. Meanwhile, mince @garlic{1%clove} (use the other as
you like).

Add @green beans{12%ounce} to #pot with boiling water and cook until tender but still
a little crisp, ~{3-4%minutes}. Drain and return to #pot along with @butter{1/2%tablespoon}
and a pinch of garlic. Toss until butter melts and coats green beans. Season with
salt, pepper, and more garlic (to taste, but save a little for the glaze).

Add @butter{3%tablespoon}, @cinnamon{1%teaspoon}, and @maple syrup{1%tablespoon} (we'll
use the rest later) to #bowl with sweet potatoes. Using a #potato masher{} or #fork,
mash sweet potatoes until mostly smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Cover to keep
warm and set aside.

> Add a pinch of brown sugar if you have it and like your potatoes extra sweet.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add @garlic{1%clove}(minced)
and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Pour in @balsamic vinegar{3%tablespoon}
(we sent more) and remove #pan from heat. Let bubble and reduce until slightly syrupy,
about ~{1%minute}. Return #pan to medium heat and add remaining @maple syrup{1%tablespoon}.
Simmer until thick and glaze-like, about ~{2%minutes}.

Add chicken to #pan and turn to coat in glaze. Remove pan from heat. Divide sweet
potatoes, green beans, and chicken between #plates{}. Sprinkle sweet potatoes with
@pecans{2%ounce}. Drizzle any remaining glaze over chicken and serve.